content: Master a few or all notes at once. Adjustable. Short and engaging.

A wonderful concept BUT I have a Samsung S9 and the app says it was built for an older system - it did offer me a refund. I need to be able to use the feature whereby I can send pupils the notes they need to practise. It is also a pity that Apple products have more features. As this is a teaching app, it would be helpful for teachers who have Android and their pupils who have Apple (or vice versa) to have exactly the same app and EVEN more essential due to remote learning in lockdown.
It's great, my students love it
It's so easy and boring

Please provide equal functionality in the android version. It is not correct to provide more features on a ios version. Are there any developer roadblocks you are facing while coding the android version?

Useless compared to the iOS version; I bought this after using it in a cello lesson - having it call out notes and then play them was a really handy exercise, particularly with random keys and accidentals. The Android version seems to have around 10% of the features.
Why do we have to pay but i like it

I was asked to purchase this ap by my daughter's piano teacher. Not enough of the keyboard shows to correctly answer the notes. We can not connect to her teacher because we do not use Apple products and she does. There are other options on Apple products. We do not use apple products. When the ap is updated to work the same on Android as Apple I will change my review.

The app is fine, but there are so many more features that they haven't gotten for android users. My 7 yo daughter saw that there was a unicorn version that we can't get on our android. She's been bitter ever since. Please undate for android users too!!! Please!!

I loved this app and was so happy with it until I just had a look at the apple version. WHAT IN THE WORLD?! Why is there such a difference? I feel cheated! Please get those functions available for Android! Especially the microphone function, where you can play notes on an actual piano. Please please please!
Like the new version with more notes and clefs but sometimes freezes my phone and I have to remove battery to reboot. Android on Sony Xperia. Still no reindeer on android?
Without a listen mode, this app is useless. Overall feel of the app is summed up with one word: cheap!
I guess they never update the Android version. Too bad. The iOS version has a lot more features.
Unless I just can't find it, it doesn't have the listen mode like the ios version...
This game helps u with the basics of learning your notes

Great starter activity for the early years. Would love to see optional extra notes eg more Leger line notes, crotchets and alto/tenor clefs. My daughter has used this for open strings on cello. I was recommending for a friend learning the violin and realised you can't get G3 in the treble clef which is the lowest open string. Also i would change the "booing" sound for a wrong answer... a bit harsh!
It's the basic note reading app for kids, helps for beginners...
This app makes flashcards a lot more fun. Super quick feedback and changes on a bug fix! Thanks!
Always Freezing

Very annoying app. Freezes on my Samsung s5. Waste of time.
It doesn't teach you trombone notes
I can't use any option after installation waste of money      REFUND MY MONEY
App crashes immediately after loading

I'm using a Lenovo S8-50 tablet, running KitKat 4.4.2. Game freezes when playing. I set it to treble clef spaces only and the game stopped after a few notes. Tried again and the game froze near the end as the clapping sound effect started. Both times the background sound kept going as if the game was still playing but the animation stopped and the note wouldn't change to a new one. It's a shame because it'd be more fun for my students than plain old flashcards. Edit: dropped to 1 star due to no fix.
Great game!
I really wanted to install this app but it can't install!!!!!!!!:-(
Great app.
Kids seem to like the program.   Easily configured to work specific notes or note ranges.  A worthwhile addition to the Android platform.

Tried a lot of apps on learning notes on staff.. So far I found this is the best one out there
I love this app when it works.  It is nearly perfect. However it crashes and glitches all the time. My daughter is so frustrated that she won't play it anymore. Please fix it!
I keeps freezing on both my android devices.....frustrating

I am right in the middle with this one. The game is fun and my piano kids light up when they get to play it, but it does freeze. It gets a little frustrating to keep backing out or reopening the game just so my student can play a couple rounds. I'm keeping it at this point only because it is fun....when it works.
I love the app. It is a great tool for learning note names.  But, it keeps getting stuck on my Android Samsung Galaxy Note 3.
Its challening
Good way for my kid to learn but it gets stuck a lot please fix glitches!
Total waste of $s. Great idea, but hangs after the second note. Very discouraging. Not working, should never have been released. Galaxy Note 3

Was good but after last update constantly freezes after a few notes. Turning off sound helps a bit but not much. Running on an Xperia z tablet Please fix!
As others are reporting it crashes.  I want a refund...
replyContent: Hello Dave, I'm currently debugging an issue that certain users are having on KitKat. Could you please confirm what version of Android you are using? Also, does turning off the sound IN THE APP (by going to the settings icon and then tapping the speaker icon so that it turns red) have any effect on crashing? Thanks for your help! - Luke

content: Nexus 5. Android 4.4.2. Hangs during race.
replyContent: Chris, could you check and see if turning off the sound IN THE APP has any effect on stability? You can test this by tapping the settings icon and then disabling the sound by tapping the speaker icon so that it turns red. Thanks for your help. - Luke

content: I just downloaded new upgrade and it keeps freezing and failing. Please fix quick cause my students will really miss this game.  Haven't been able to try out all the new stuff but it sounds great.  I'm on a nexus 5.
replyContent: I'm looking into your issue. Please let me know which version of Android you are running and where you were in the app when the crash occurred (choosing notes, running a race, etc). Be as specific as possible. Also, please confirm that you are not on a rooted device. I'll work on fixing any issues ASAP. Thanks for the feedback! - Luke Bartolomeo
